#eNCA's Dasen Thathaih has the details. #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Judge Piet Koen has recused himself from former President Jacob Zuma's corruption trial. He says there may be reasonable apprehension of bias in how the case has been treated. The judge says it is in the interest of justice that he withdraws from the matter. eNCA senior reporter Dasen Thathiah has the details in the video above.